-- Credit Agricole Beats Rivals as M&A Clients’ Shares Perform Best
-- B y   A n n a - L o u i s e   J a c k s o n
-- 2010-10-01T04:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/credit-agricole-beats-rivals-as-m-a-clients-shares-perform-best.html
Shares of companies that relied on
 Credit Agricole SA  for advice on acquisitions performed better
on average after the deals were announced than those of
corporations that hired other investment banks, according to
data compiled by Bloomberg Rankings.  Bloomberg looked at 100 $5 billion-plus deals completed
from May 2005 to May 2008. Investment banks were ranked on the
average performance of their clients’ stocks against peer
indexes from 30 days before the companies unveiled an
acquisition to two years after it was completed.  A summary of the ranking is below. For the complete list,
click here. For details on acquisitions used in the rankings and
the investment banks’ other deals, click on the links below.   ===============================================================  Advisers Whose             Number of Deals     Average  Clients Fared Worst                         Excess Return*
 ===============================================================
 1      Merrill Lynch & Co.            14          -14.02
 2      UBS AG                          8          -13.87
 3      Bear Stearns Cos.               3          -12.13
 4      Societe Generale                3          -11.05
 5      Bank of America Corp.           6          - 5.27
================================================================
